- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a method to improve the performance and convergence time of a Generalized Linear Model by decoupling the learning rates of first order and second order features. This falls under the domain of machine learning, making cs.LG the most likely category.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed method involves using an Empirical Bayes approach to compute a hierarchical prior, which is a common technique in Bayesian inference and artificial intelligence.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the challenges of optimizing over sparse data, which is a common problem in data structures and algorithms.
- cs.ST (Statistics): The paper uses statistical techniques such as Empirical Bayes to improve the performance of the model.
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the use of information theory to improve the performance of the model by focusing on learning first order weights first.
